solution:
Each number from 1 to 6 has probability $\dfrac16$ of being rolled, so the expected value is \begin{align*}
E &= \left(\dfrac{1}{6}\times \$1^2\right) + \left(\dfrac{1}{6}\times \$2^2\right) + \cdots + \left(\dfrac{1}{6} \times \$6^2\right) \\
&= \dfrac{1}{6}(\$1 + \$4 + \$9 + \$16 + \$25 + \$36) \\
&= \$\dfrac{91}{6} \\
& \approx \boxed{\$15.17}.
\end{align*}

problem:
There exists a constant $c,$ so that among all chords $\overline{AB}$ of the parabola $y = x^2$ passing through $C = (0,c),$
\[t = \frac{1}{AC} + \frac{1}{BC}\]is a fixed constant.  Find the constant $t.$

[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

real parab (real x) {
  return(x^2);
}

pair A, B, C;

A = (1.7,parab(1.7));
B = (-1,parab(-1));
C = extension(A,B,(0,0),(0,1));

draw(graph(parab,-2,2));
draw(A--B);
draw((0,0)--(0,4));

dot("$A$", A, E);
dot("$B$", B, SW);
dot("$(0,c)$", C, NW);
[/asy]

